@30="Dispel Magic (Abjuration) 
Level: 3
Sphere: Protection 
Range: Visual range of caster
Duration: Special 
Casting Time: 6 
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: Special

When a priest casts this spell, it has a chance to negate magic it comes in contact with, as follows: First, it removes spells and spell-like effects (including those from magical device and innate abilities) up to the 6th circle on creatures or objects. Second, it neutralizes magical potions. Third, it can render golems inactive for one round if they fail a saving throw versus spell.

Each effect or potion in the spell's area is checked to determine if it is dispelled. The chance to dispel depends on the difference in level between the intended recipient and the caster. The base chance is 50%, if the caster is of higher level than the individual under a dispellable effect, the chance increases by 3% per level above to maximum of 95%; conversely if the caster is of lower level, the chance is reduced by 3% per level below to a minimum of 5%. If the target has levels in more than one character class, the highest is checked."
@31="Remove Magic (Abjuration) 
Level: 3
Range: Visual range of caster
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 3 
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: Special

This is the combat version of dispel magic; it will only affect opponents. When a wizard casts this spell, it has a chance to negate magic it comes in contact with, as follows: First, it removes spells and spell-like effects (including those from magical device and innate abilities) up to the 6th circle on enemies in the area. Second, it neutralizes magical potions. Third, it can render attacking golems inactive for one round if they fail a saving throw versus spell.

Each effect or potion in the spell's area is checked to determine if it is dispelled. The chance to dispel depends on the difference in level between the hostile creature and the caster. The base chance is 50%, if the caster is of higher level than an enemy under a dispellable effect, the chance increases by 3% per level above to maximum of 95%; conversely if the caster is of lower level, the chance is reduced by 3% per level below to a minimum of 5%. If the target has levels in more than one character class, the highest is checked."
